name: challenge2
description: Given an array of numbers write a function to move all 0;s to the end of it while maintaining the relative order of the non-zero elements. This must be done in-place (ie. without making a copy of the array) and while minimizing the total number of operations. Example: Input: [0,1,0,3,12] Output:[1,3,12,0,0]
author: Alexander Kutz
